      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MAXIMUM SUNSET (1) was safely held on debut after settling well back when seventh (23.02) at Warrnambool over 390m. Gets the coveted rails draw for the first time. This looks easier and expected to improve sharply. INDIAN STAR (4) jumped from the middle and safely held on debut at Geelong over 400m (23.68). Meets a moderate line up and should do much better. WEST END BOY (8) ran a nice race on debut when hitting the frame, finishing third (23.18) at Geelong over 400m. Can feature again with the right run. BRITTLES (5) makes debut for the David Long kennel. No favours with the draw and will need to begin well. Expected to produce a bold debut.",
